      "content": {
        "title": "Wrist Ligament and TFCC Injuries — Core Principles",
        "definition": "Tears of intrinsic wrist ligaments and triangular fibrocartilage complex causing ulnar-sided wrist pain and instability.",
        "summary": "Scapholunate dissociation leads to DISI deformity. TFCC tears cause DRUJ instability; foveal tears have worse prognosis."
      },
